hooks.prompt:
Review the conversation transcript for repeated corrections — cases where the user corrected Claude on the same thing more than once this session (e.g., 'I already told you...', 'no, like I said before...', correcting the same mistake twice). Also look for explicit but unhandled 'remember this' requests.

If you find repeated corrections or unhandled remember requests, respond with:
{"decision": "block", "reason": "Detected repeated correction or unhandled remember request. Offering to persist the learning.", "systemMessage": "Before finishing, you noticed a repeated correction or an unhandled 'remember this' request in this session. Ask the user if they'd like you to persist this learning using the remember-that skill so it carries across sessions. Be specific about what you detected."}

If no repeated corrections or unhandled requests are found, respond with:
{"decision": "approve"}
